<LegalLayout
  title="Cookie Policy"
  description="Learn about how AUXO Data Labs uses cookies and similar tracking technologies on our website."
  lastUpdated="January 10, 2026"
>
  <h2>1. What Are Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files placed on your device that help us operate and improve our website, auxodata.com ("Site"). They are widely used to make websites work more efficiently and provide information to website owners.
  </p>

  <h2>2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    AUXO Data Labs uses cookies and similar tracking technologies to enable essential functionality (login, preferences), measure Site performance and behaviour, personalize content and marketing, and enhance security and fraud detection.
  </p>
  <p>
    <span class="highlight">We implement Google Consent Mode v2</span>, ensuring that cookies respect your consent preferences and comply with privacy regulations including GDPR, CCPA, and UAE PDPL. Analytics and marketing cookies are only activated after you provide explicit consent.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Your Choices</h2>
  <p>
    On your first visit, a cookie banner lets you accept, reject, or manage preferences. You may adjust preferences anytime or disable cookies in your browser. <span class="highlight">Note that disabling certain cookies may affect website functionality.</span>
  </p>

  <h2>4. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
  <h3>4.1 Essential Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They enable core functionality such as security, network management, and accessibility. <span class="highlight">You cannot opt out of essential cookies as they are required for the Site to operate.</span>
  </p>

  <h3>4.2 Analytics / Performance Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by collecting and reporting information anonymously. This helps us measure Site usage to improve performance and user experience.
  </p>

  <h3>4.3 Marketing / Advertising Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    These cookies are used to track visitors across websites to deliver relevant advertisements and track the effectiveness of our marketing campaigns.
  </p>

